A group, Miyeti Allah Wallidira, Waansa Nigeria Peace Initiative and Global Peace Initiative have called for truce ahead of Ijaw Youth Council peaceful election. In a statement jointly signed by the president, Miyeti Allah Wallidira, Yusuf Ardo, president, Waansa Nigeria, Engr George Chidi and Global Peace Initiative executive director, Sadiq Badamasi and made available to LEADERSHIP in Abuja, the group noted that a peaceful election by IYC in the South-south region will herald and guarantee a people-oriented leadership. It noted that sequel to the commencement of preparation towards a two days national peace round table with ethnic nationalities in the country the group lauded IYC harmonisation aimed at providing one unified leadership. The statement reads in part: ‘’We are optimistic that this is the beginning of genuine peace in Niger Delta going by the role Ijaw Youth Council plays in the area of peacebuilding and conflict resolution in the south south region. ‘’As northern traditional rulers, Southwest Obas, chiefs and Niger Delta groups are preparing for this all-important national peace round table we appeal to crisis entrepreneurs to stay away from IYC as failure to do that will attract severe consequence from the groups working with Ijaw Youth Council for a peaceful united one Nigeria.’’ The statement also appealed to the federal government to pay close attention to land borders as air transport has reduced to contain coronavirus infections.